From: Yang Shi <yang.shi@windriver.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Sep 2010 15:57:32 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] PM: SDHCI: enable the DMA during resume

Enable the DMA snoop from deep sleep.

Signed-off-by: Yang Shi <yang.shi@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-of-core.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-of-core.c b/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-of-core.c
index 78765f0..fb57ca5 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-of-core.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-of-core.c
@@ -98,6 +98,7 @@ static int sdhci_of_resume(struct of_device *ofdev)
 {
 	struct sdhci_host *host = dev_get_drvdata(&ofdev->dev);
 
+	sdhci_esdhc.ops.enable_dma(host);
 	return mmc_resume_host(host->mmc);
 }
 
